column1: # article: Provenance analysis of the Voirons Flysch (Gurnigel nappe, Haute-Savoie, France): Stratigraphic and paleogeographic implications
# journal name: International Journal of Earth-Sciences
# author: Ragusa J, Kindler P, Segvic B and Ospina-Ostios LM
# description: Framework composition of the Voirons Flysch following the Gazzi-Dickinson method
# Mineral abbreviations are based on the compilation of Whitney and Evans (2010)
# unit: VS = Voirons Sandstone Fm., VC = Vouan Conglomerate Fm., BM = Boëge Marl Fm., BS = Bruant Sandstone Fm., AS = Allinges Sandstone

# Quartz: Qms = single monocrytalline quartz, Qps = non tectonised polycrystalline quartz, QpT = tectonised polycrystalline quartz, Qr = quartz in rock-fragments (m=metamorphic, g=plutonic, v=volcanic)
# Feldpars: Ks = single K-feldspar, Kr = K-feldspar in rock-fragments, An = anorthite Anr = anorthite in rock fragments, Ab = albite, Abr = albite in rock-fragments
# Lithics: Lci = mudstone to wackestone fragments, Lch = chert, Lmf(1-5) = metapsammite/metafelsite grains, Lmp(1-5) = metapelite grains, Lmb1 = metabasite grains
# C = calcite cement, Bc = total carbonate bioclast
# D = dense minerals, M = micas, Chl = chlorite, Glt = glauconite, Op = opaque grains, Ph = phosphate, Si = silice
